## Technical Research Methodology

### Technology Assessment

```text
Technical Evaluation Process
├── 1. Define Requirements
│   ├── Functional requirements
│   ├── Non-functional requirements (performance, security)
│   └── Constraints (budget, timeline, skills)
├── 2. Landscape Survey
│   ├── Identify all plausible options
│   ├── Categorize by approach
│   └── Quick viability filter
├── 3. Deep Evaluation
│   ├── Documentation quality
│   ├── Community health (GitHub activity, SO questions)
│   ├── Maintenance status
│   ├── Security track record
│   └── Performance benchmarks
├── 4. Proof of Concept
│   ├── Test key requirements
│   ├── Identify hidden complexity
│   └── Validate claims
└── 5. Decision
    ├── Weighted scoring matrix
    ├── Risk assessment
    └── Recommendation with rationale
```

### Debugging and Troubleshooting Research

1. **Reproduce** - Confirm the exact conditions
2. **Isolate** - Narrow to smallest failing case
3. **Search** - Error messages, stack traces, exact symptoms
4. **Read** - Documentation, source code, issue trackers
5. **Experiment** - Systematic hypothesis testing
6. **Ask** - Stack Overflow, forums, colleagues (after researching)

